SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 941
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to recognize and honor Michael Patrick Leahy.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should recognize
those individuals whose professional achievements and civic engagement contribute to the
public discourse and the civic life of our State and nation; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy individual is Michael Patrick Leahy, a respected
journalist, author, and radio host, who has distinguished himself through many years of
dedication to journalism and civic education; and
WHEREAS, for the past fifteen years, Mr. Leahy has been a Tennessee-based
journalist, first serving as a reporter for Breitbart News before expanding his work in the field of
independent journalism; and
WHEREAS, nine years ago he founded The Tennessee Star, a Nashville-based news
organization through which he continues to serve as Chief Executive Officer and Editor-in-Chief,
providing news coverage and commentary on matters of public interest to the citizens of this
State; and
WHEREAS, in 2025, Mr. Leahy and his colleagues at The Tennessee Star were
honored with the Dao Prize for best local journalism in the country, a recognition that highlights
the impact of their work in the field of local reporting; and
WHEREAS, in addition to his work as a journalist, Michael Patrick Leahy has served for
eight years as a radio show host in Nashville, engaging listeners in discussions on public affairs
and civic issues; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Leahy is also an author who has contributed to civic education through
his work Guide to the Constitution and Bill of Rights for Secondary School Students, a book he
SJR0941
015566
- 1 -

coauthored to help young people better understand the principles of American government and
constitutional liberty; and
WHEREAS, inspired by this work, in 2017 he founded the National Constitution Bee, an
annual scholarship competition designed to encourage high school students to deepen their
knowledge of the United States Constitution and the Bill of Rights; and
WHEREAS, in October 2026, Mr. Leahy will serve as master of ceremonies for the
National Constitution Bee to be held in Brentwood, continuing his commitment to promoting civic
literacy and constitutional education among the next generation of Americans; and
WHEREAS, through his work as a journalist, broadcaster, author, and civic educator,
Michael Patrick Leahy has contributed to the ongoing conversation about public affairs and
constitutional principles, and it is fitting that we recognize his efforts and accomplishments; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we recognize and honor Michael Patrick Leahy for
his contributions to journalism, civic education, and public discourse in the State of Tennessee.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
